HEADWORD: Helicin
<hw>Hel"i*cin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
glucoside obtained as a white crystalline substance by partial oxidation
of salicin, from a willow (<spn>Salix Helix</spn> of
Linnaeus.)</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

